<body>
   <p> A quick and simple chili recipe for you to enjoy</p>
   <h1>Steves Chili recipe</h1>
   <img src="Chili-2.jpg">
   
  <table border="0">
     <tr>
       <th>Ingredients</th>
       <th>Quantity</th>
     </tr>
     <tr>
       <td>Ground Beef</td>
       <td>2 lbs</td>
     </tr>
     <tr>
        <td>Kidney Beans</td>
        <td>4 cans</td>
     </tr>   
     <tr>
       <td>Bell Peppers</td>
       <td>2</td>
     </tr>
     <tr>
        <td>Tomatoes</td>
        <td>2 cans</td>
     </tr>
     <tr>
        <td>Onion</td>
        <td>1 medium</td>
     </tr>
     <tr>
        <td>Cayenne Pepper</td>
        <td>2 teaspoon</td>
     </tr>
     <tr>
         <td>Chili powder</td>
         <td>1 teaspoon</td>
     </tr>
   </table><br>
   <table border="0">
   	  <tr>
   	  	<th>Gear needed</th>
   	  </tr>
   	  <tr>
   	    <td>8 quart stockpot</td>
   	  </tr>
   	  <tr>
   	    <td>Large spoon</td>
   	  </tr>
   	  <tr>
   	     <td>can opener</td>
   	  </tr>
   	  <tr>
   	    <td>1 tsp measuring spoon</td>
   	  </tr>
   	  <tr>
   	    <td>Sharp knife</td>
   	  </tr>
   	  <tr>
   	    <td>cutting board</td>
   	  </tr>

   </table>
   <p><strong>Instructions for cooking</strong></p>
   <ol>
     <li>Brown the ground beef</li>
     <li>Dice the onion while meat is cooking</li>
     <li>Open all the cans with the can opener</li>
     <li>When the meat is through cooking dump all the cans into the pot</li>
     <li>Measure the Chili powder and cayenne pepper and dump into the pot</li>
     <li>Lower heat and slow simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally</li>
    </ol> 

